---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Palchat – Ideas & Tiny Tools">
  <main class="relative min-h-screen overflow-hidden bg-slate-950 text-slate-50">
    <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 -z-10">
      <div class="absolute -left-40 top-0 h-80 w-80 rounded-full bg-sky-500/20 blur-3xl sm:-left-32 sm:h-96 sm:w-96" />
      <div class="absolute bottom-0 right-0 h-80 w-80 rounded-full bg-purple-500/20 blur-3xl sm:h-96 sm:w-96" />
      <div class="absolute inset-x-0 top-40 h-64 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top,_rgba(56,189,248,0.18),_transparent_60%)]" />
    </div>

    <section
      id="why"
      class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pb-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8"
    >
      <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-4">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-100 sm:text-4xl">
          A dependency trap dressed up as efficiency
        </h1>

        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
          AI that does the work for you feels like a win. It is fast and cheap. But it can also slowly weaken how well
          you understand and control your own business.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-3 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70 p-4 text-sm text-slate-200 sm:text-base">
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-100 sm:text-lg">What you gain</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300">
            You save money. You move faster. You can serve more people. The $1k vs $40k story is real and easy to see.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 rounded-2xl border border-amber-500/40 bg-slate-900/70 p-4 text-sm text-slate-200 sm:text-base">
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-amber-200 sm:text-lg">What you slowly lose</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li>
              <span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">You lose understanding.</span>
              <span class="text-slate-300">
                {' '}
                A human explains things over time. With AI, the work happens in a black box. You get a result, but you
                cannot really explain it.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">You lose custody.</span>
              <span class="text-slate-300">
                {' '}
                Your data and process now live inside a tool you rent. You do not own the workflow. You borrow it.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">You lose resilience.</span>
              <span class="text-slate-300">
                {' '}
                If a person leaves, another can step in. If a tool dies, raises prices, or gets bought, you may lose the
                memory of how your own business works.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">You lose the human buffer.</span>
              <span class="text-slate-300">
                {' '}
                A person can say “this looks odd, want to talk?” An AI just processes what you type and moves on.
              </span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 rounded-2xl border border-sky-500/40 bg-slate-900/70 p-4 text-sm text-slate-200 sm:text-base">
          <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-sky-200 sm:text-lg">The deeper problem</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300">
            One cheap tool looks fine. Ten cheap tools across your work and life means you quietly hand off your own
            skills to ten different companies. You do not see the cost until you cannot live without them.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-300">
            The problem is not AI itself. The problem is the belief that cheaper and easier is always better. Dependency
            has a price. It just does not show up on the invoice.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="border-t border-slate-800 bg-slate-950/90">
      <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl flex-col gap-4 px-4 py-6 text-xs text-slate-400 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <div class="flex h-7 w-7 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-tr from-sky-400 to-purple-500 text-xs font-semibold text-slate-950">
            P
          </div>
          <span>© {new Date().getFullYear()} Palchat. All rights reserved.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="/about" class="hover:text-sky-300">About</a>
          <a href="/comments" class="hover:text-sky-300">Tech demo</a>
          <a href="mailto:hello@palchat.org" class="hover:text-sky-300">Contact</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </main>
</Layout>
